definition: to (a place)/until (a time)/up to/to go/to arrive/(verb complement denoting completion or result of an action)

sentences.english: They raised the price of a one way lift ticket from $24 to $26.
sentences.chinese: 他們把纜車單程票價從24美元漲到26美元。

sentences.english: They jumped the registration fees from ￡20 to ￡50.
sentences.chinese: 他們把註冊費從20英鎊漲到50英鎊。

sentences.english: The water is coming up to the bank.
sentences.chinese: 河水漲到跟河岸相平了。
